Hourly Dissolved Oxygen

Chelsey Wegener

11/3/2020

Average hourly dissolved oxygen

Data at EOS are collected every 6 minutes, data at China Camp and Richardson Bay is collected every 15 minutes. No dissolved data available at Fort Point. I’m going to convert all data to average hourly (60min) so that everything is consitent. The outliers were removed before this step. Outliers detected by QC flag and +/- 2sd from 7 day rolling mean. Using averageTime function in openair package to calculate hourly mean. For timeAverage function to work, you need a date or POSIXct column named “date”. interval = frequency of data collection.

China Camp

cc<-read.csv("C:/Users/chels/Box Sync/Thesis/Data/Working data/Bouy data/cc_do_clean.csv", header = TRUE, sep=",", fileEncoding="UTF-8-BOM", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

names(cc)[names(cc) == "DateTimeStamp"] <- "date"

cc$date<-as.POSIXct(cc$date, format = c("%m/%d/%Y %H:%M"))


cc_h_do<- timeAverage(cc,
            avg.time="1 hour",
            data.thresh = 0,
            statistic = "mean",
            interval = "15 min",
            remove.calm = FALSE,
            type = "default")
## Warning: Missing dates detected, removing 12 lines
## Warning in checkPrep(mydata, vars, type = "default", remove.calm = FALSE, :
## Detected data with Daylight Saving Time, converting to UTC/GMT
cc_g<-cc_h_do %>% ggplot(aes(x=date, y=DO_mgl, color=DO_mgl))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.5)+ylim(0,20)+
  labs(title="Hourly dissolved oxygen from China Camp",
       subtitle="01/01/2017 - 12/31/2019",
       caption= "data courtesy of NERR")

Eos

eos<-read.csv("C:/Users/chels/Box Sync/Thesis/Data/Working data/Bouy data/eos_do_clean.csv", header = TRUE, sep=",", fileEncoding="UTF-8-BOM", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

names(eos)[names(eos) == "datetime"] <- "date"

eos$date<-as.POSIXct(eos$date, format = c("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ"))



eos_h_do<- timeAverage(eos,
            avg.time="1 hour",
            data.thresh = 0,
            statistic = "mean",
            interval = "6 min",
            remove.calm = FALSE,
            type = "default")
## Warning in checkPrep(mydata, vars, type = "default", remove.calm = FALSE, :
## Detected data with Daylight Saving Time, converting to UTC/GMT

  geom_point(alpha=0.5)+ylim(0,20)+
  labs(title="Hourly dissolved oxygen from EOS resesarch pier",
